article_title: Powell May Be Jets’ Best Pass-Catching Back in a Decade
article_text:
The Jets have ignored their tight ends as a third option in the passing game this season behind receivers Brandon Marshall and Eric Decker. But they may have found a new tight end-like receiving weapon—except he’s 5-foot-11 and plays running back.

Bilal Powell has emerged as a legitimate receiving threat, hauling in eight passes for 91 yards in last Sunday’s win over the Giants. His 13 targets in that game were the most for a Jets...
